cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a novel neural network structure for better modeling long term dependency in sequential data. The proposed structure, called Higher Order Recurrent Neural Networks (HORNNs), is applicable to a variety of sequence modeling tasks, including language modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, since the paper proposes a new neural network structure, it is likely to be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision), which are all related to developing and improving machine learning models.
